# Performance and Verify Gates

- Maintain stable geometry (no accidental CLS): reserve media space and avoid layout-jumping edits.
- Keep animation performance-safe: prefer `transform`/`opacity`; preserve existing physics/timings.
- Do not introduce non-passive `wheel`/`touchstart`/`touchmove` listeners unless strictly required.
- For changes affecting scroll/animation, verify lifecycle cleanup (timers, rAF, observers, listeners).
- Use section root isolation and layering discipline to avoid cross-section paint/stacking regressions.
- After substantive edits, run verification commands and report results:
  - `npm run build` (required)
  - lint/typecheck/tests when relevant
- If verification fails, fix or report blocker explicitly; never present unverified changes as complete.
